Anniversary of PRC observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 1 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate signed articles to the 53rd anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
 The foundation of the PRC was an epochal event which brought about a fundamental turn in the historic development of the Chinese people and carving out their destiny, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese people made great achievements in their efforts to create a new life and build new socialist China in the past 53 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are now making positive efforts to step up the modernization of the country under the leadership of the Communist Party of China and build socialism with Chinese characteristics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese government is paying special attention to realizing socio-political stability and unity and striving to reunify the whole country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 China has pursued its independent and sovereign foreign policy to develop its relations with Asian countries and other countries and strengthen its position and influence in the international arena. The Chinese people have taken a new road of advance to attain a higher goal of the socialist modernization drive with Chinese characteristics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We sincerely wish the Chinese people greater success in their work for the prosperity and development and complete reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says the Korean people believe that the DPRK-China friendship will grow stronger in the future, too.

Russian artistes see performance given by artistes of Ministry of People's Security 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 1 (KCNA) -- The State Academy Ensemble of Ministry of Interior of Russia saw a song and dance performance given by the ensemble of the DPRK Ministry of People's Security at the Ponghwa Art Theater on Monday.
 Among the audience were Viktor Eliseyev, head of the ensemble, and its members and Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov and staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean ensemble's repertoire included Korean songs and dances "Song of General Kim Jong Il," "As general is a crack shot we never miss targets" and "At the spring" and Russian songs "Day of Victory," "Ryabinushka in the Ural mountains". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was presented to the performers in congratulation of their successful performance.

Chinese Ambassador hosts reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 1 (KCNA) -- Wu Donghe, Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK, hosted a reception at the Okryu Restaurant on Monday evening on the occasion of the 53rd anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
 The ambassador in his speech said that the foundation of the PRC recorded a new page in the history of the Chinese people, and introduced successes china achieved after the foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) and the government of the DPRK had exerted all efforts to accelerate the economic development, ease tension on the Korean Peninsula and strengthen the external relations, he sincerely hoped that everything would go well in the DPRK and the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea would be realized. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, in his speech said that over the last 53 years since the foundation of the PRC the Chinese people had worked hard to create a new life, thus building a prosperous socialist state on the vast land of China, once backward and poverty-stricken. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the firm stand and will of the WPK and the government of the DPRK to steadily consolidate and develop the DPRK-China friendship, he said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We together with the Chinese comrades will continue making efforts to further develop the bilateral friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Invited to the reception were Kim Su Hak, minister of public health who is the chairman of the c.c., the DPRK-China friendship association, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys from different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Liu Zhigang, Chinese consul general to Chongjin, also hosted a reception on Monday on the same occasion.

Great unity of nation called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 1 (KCNA) -- The cause of national reunification is a common cause of the Korean nation to bring happiness and prosperity to the nation, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our cause of reunification is a worthwhile patriotic work to reconnect the severed blood ties of the nation and demonstrate the dignity and might of the reunified Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The destiny and development of the nation can be guaranteed only when independent reunification is achieved to realize independence of the nation and it is an expression of most ardent patriotism to work hard to attain it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If our nation is to preserve its national character as a homogeneous nation with a long history and carve out its destiny independently, it is necessary to rejoin the severed blood ties of the nation and reappear as such. Great national unity should be achieved to realize this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Achieving this unity is the best way of putting an end to the tragedy of national division and reunifying Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The territorial partition and the national split have spelled unspeakable national disasters to the fellow countrymen and blocked the uniform development of the country. it is only foreign forces that fish in troubled waters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when the country is reunified can the Korean nation pool its wisdom and efforts and enlist and use the resources and economic potentials in the north and the south in a uniform manner to turn Korea into a prosperous country. Reunified Korea would emerge the world's strongest country both in name and reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north, the south and overseas should make more energetic efforts to build a reunified and prosperous powerful country on this land under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.

Anecdotes about Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 1 (KCNA) -- It happened in August Juche 89 (2000) when delegates of South Korean media organizations visited Pyongyang.
 When Kim Jong Il received them, they told him that the north could make a big money if it advanced abroad by promoting joint ventures with other countries in the domains of animated cartoons and computer software as it had already reached the world standards in the fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laughing broadly, he said that if the north and the south launched joint ventures in these fields the profit would all belong to Korea with each side taking half of it. Then, why should we make joint ventures with other countries, he asked.
 The delegates were deeply moved by the leader putting the interests of the nation above anything else. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another anecdote about him is related to cosmetics produced at the Sinuiju cosmetics factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is a certificate at a sample room of the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the certificate of a gold medal the Nowana-branded cosmetics won at the international cosmetics festival. It was a pride of the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il visited the factory a few years ago. Looking at the certificate he said nothing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He just took measures to modernize the factory to produce and supply high quality cosmetics to the people although it was a very difficult time when the country had to tighten its belt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After his visit, the brand was renamed spring fragrance, widely accepted by the people, and the products have been fully supplied to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il visited the factory again afterwards. Factory officials gave him something to read. It was a letter sent by a woman living in a mountainous county in Ryanggang Province to thank the factory for face cream and powder of the spring fragrance brand it produced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Greatly satisfied to read the letter, he said the letter was just a certificate the factory should receive.

Pictures carved on stones popular
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 1 (KCNA) -- There is the Amnokgang Studio carving pictures on stones in Pothonggang district, Pyongyang, drawing an increasing number of visitors.
 They can have their color or black and white pictures carved on stones in a few minutes according to their wishes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pictures of diverse sizes and varieties done on stones are available there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These kinds of pictures are very popular among visitors as they can be permanently preserved and are characterized by their truthful depiction, delicate workmanship and peculiar formative artistry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They show keen interest in pictures of their lovely children and parents in their youth, souvenir pictures on birthdays and weddings and various kinds of landscape pictures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The studio is staffed with competent technicians and equipped with up-to-date technical facilities including computerized machines to carve pictures on stones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The services made by the studio showcase the good manners and customs of the Korean people and more diverse needs of their cultural life.
